{
  "stem": "21626.4",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "It-- actually, before we moved to Wales, I-- I recall very vividly one night in March, 1943.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We older ones were allowed to listen to 9 o'clock news.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And I remember being there with my friends and listening.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And it was on that occasion when the man who spoke on the radio announced clearly and precisely what was happening to Jews in the camps.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Until that day, I hoped that my parents were still in the staging post-- that garrison town of Terezin, or Theresienstadt, as it's popularly called-- where I felt they may be living comparatively normal life-- at least that came over from the news which we got.",
      "word_count": 46
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But of course, after hearing about the deprivation and the horrors of the camps, one could never be sure where they were.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And life for us, who left their parents behind, was never the same after that night.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "We have to live with this new fear.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And it was a terrible fear.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And once again, I found it invaluable to have the support of the children and the teachers around me.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And I cried for my sis, who was so alone in a completely English environment-- of people who might-- who cared for her, but could not understand no more than the Rainfords could or the Campions could.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "You know, they sort of felt-- even my sister felt that such atrocities, as we were hearing, surely could not have gone on.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "I mean, one human being could not do this to another human being.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And I think many people felt like this.",
      "word_count": 8
    }
  ],
